	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Author is going to need exact step-by-step reproduction documentation to figure this out.  A save state immediately prior (say within 10 seconds or so), followed by exact and very clear instructions on how to achieve it, is necessary.  Without that, I can assure you rdanbrook will prioritise that ticket extremely low (I know I would).<br /><br />To me though, it looks like more &quot;oh great, more of THIS crap&quot; PPU nonsense, as in going to take a ton of man hours just to figure out what's going on.  There's a whole series of graphical corruption that happens (meaning it's not just a palette thing), so for all I know it could be a timing-sensitive thing, or some $2002/$2005/$2006/$2007 read/write ordering quirk.<br /><br />Reminder to folks: Nestopia plays, oh I don't know, ~97% of all games reliably, so please keep that in mind.  All that ever gets reported these days are edge cases.  I think that's worth taking into consideration / remembering.  Same goes for many of the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Emulators#Popular" class="postlink">other major emulators</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
